  "narrative": "DRIVER\nGBP leads H4 CSM at 100 with USD at 95, both accelerating above D1 readings in a D1 Risk-Off to H4 Risk-On transition, driven by VIX compression to 17.4, S&P 500 at 7433, and Iran-US diplomatic optimism crushing safe-haven demand. GBPUSD and GBPCAD are the cleanest expressions, with GBP strength compounding against a softening DXY at 99.13, while GBPJPY benefits from JPY H4 acceleration flagging a 66 vs 45 D1 divergence that confirms JPY weakness is the short-term reality despite the D1 risk-off skeleton beneath. Gold at 4541 still bid is the counter-narrative \u2014 it conflicts with the risk-on read and warns that USDJPY upside is not clean.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nIran-US talks produce formal statement: USDJPY breaks higher as safe-haven JPY demand collapses, confirming H4 CSM divergence resolves to upside\nWTI extends below 98.85: USDCAD drops as CAD commodity correlation reasserts, fading CAD's current CSM strength\nFed speaker addresses yield compression at 3.56 on US 2Y: EURUSD accelerates higher as EUR H4 CSM at 51 vs D1 at 26 gap closes fast",
